column1: Supplementary Data 1.  Detailed peptide and spectral counts for proteins detected by MudPIT analysis of whole-cell lysates from Saccharomyces cerevisiae strains with different chromosome copy numbers
Proteins/protein groups are ranked by their frequency of detection and decreasing averaged dNSAFs values.
For each analysis, the following parameters are specified for each protein:

column3: peptide counts
total spectral counts
spectral counts for peptides shared between protein isoforms
peptide counts for peptides uniquely matching the protein
spectral counts for peptides uniquely matching the protein
spectral counts distributed according to the spectral count contribution of peptides unique to each isoform
sequence coverage
Normalized Spectral Abundance Factors, calculated based on distributed spectral counts and protein length.

column1: The number of times a protein is detected across replicate analyses is listed in the "Detected # Out of 4" columns.
dNSAF are averaged across replicate analyses ("dNSAF AVG" columns).
The columns labelled "TMHMM_Topology" and "SIGNALP" list the position of transmembrane helices and signal peptide as predicted for each protein by TMHMM and SignalP, respectively .
